==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fangle
<hw>Fan"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Fang</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>; hence, prop., a taking up a new thing.]</ety>
<def>Something new-fashioned; a foolish innovation; a gewgaw; a trifling
ornament.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fangle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fangle
<hw>Fan"gle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To fashion.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To control and new <qex>fangle</qex> the Scripture.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fangled</ent>⟦br⟧
